#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn1.41"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn1.41:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 1 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 1 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn1.41:0.2"
msgid "5. Ādittavagga "
msgstr "5. On Fire "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn1.41:0.3"
msgid "41. Ādittasutta "
msgstr "41. On Fire "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: pts2ed1.65, sc1
msgctxt "sn1.41:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "sn1.41:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn1.41:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho aññatarā devatā abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇā kevalakappaṃ jetavanaṃ obhāsetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. "
msgstr "Then, late at night, a glorious deity, lighting up the entire Jeta’s Grove, went up to the Buddha, bowed, stood to one side, "

msgctxt "sn1.41:1.4"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho sā devatā bhagavato santike imā gāthāyo abhāsi: "
msgstr "and recited these verses in the Buddha’s presence: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn1.41:2.1"
msgid "“Ādittasmiṃ agārasmiṃ, "
msgstr "“When your house is on fire, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.41:2.2"
msgid "yaṃ nīharati bhājanaṃ; "
msgstr "you rescue the pot "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.41:2.3"
msgid "Taṃ tassa hoti atthāya, "
msgstr "that’s useful, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.41:2.4"
msgid "no ca yaṃ tattha ḍayhati. "
msgstr "not the one that’s burnt. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn1.41:3.1"
msgid "Evaṃ ādittako loko, "
msgstr "And as the world is on fire "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.41:3.2"
msgid "jarāya maraṇena ca; "
msgstr "with old age and death, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.41:3.3"
msgid "Nīharetheva dānena, "
msgstr "you should rescue by giving, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.41:3.4"
msgid "dinnaṃ hoti sunīhataṃ. "
msgstr "for what’s given is rescued. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.32, pts2ed1.66, sc4
msgctxt "sn1.41:4.1"
msgid "Dinnaṃ sukhaphalaṃ hoti, "
msgstr "What’s given has happiness as its fruit, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.41:4.2"
msgid "nādinnaṃ hoti taṃ tathā; "
msgstr "but not what isn’t given. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.41:4.3"
msgid "Corā haranti rājāno, "
msgstr "Bandits take it, or rulers, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.41:4.4"
msgid "aggi ḍahati nassati. "
msgstr "it’s consumed by fire, or lost. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn1.41:5.1"
msgid "Atha antena jahati, "
msgstr "Then in the end this corpse is cast off, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.41:5.2"
msgid "Sarīraṃ sapariggahaṃ; "
msgstr "along with all your possessions. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.41:5.3"
msgid "Etadaññāya medhāvī, "
msgstr "Knowing this, a clever person "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.41:5.4"
msgid "Bhuñjetha ca dadetha ca; "
msgstr "would enjoy what they have and also give it away. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.41:5.5"
msgid "Datvā ca bhutvā ca yathānubhāvaṃ, "
msgstr "After giving and using according to their means, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.41:5.6"
msgid "Anindito saggamupeti ṭhānan”ti. "
msgstr "blameless, they go to a heavenly place.”"

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
